# Assignment System Development Patterns

## Component Development Standards

### Assignment System Components
All assignment system components should follow these patterns:

#### Context Usage
Always use the AssignmentSystemProvider for state management:
```typescript
import { useAssignmentSystem } from '@/contexts/AssignmentSystemContext'

const {
  allAssignments,
  studentAssignments,
  loading,
  createLessonAssignment,
  updateStudentAssignmentStatus
} = useAssignmentSystem()
```

#### Role-Based Rendering
Check user permissions before rendering sensitive content:
```typescript
import { useSession } from 'next-auth/react'
import { getUserRole } from '@/lib/permissions'

const { data: session } = useSession()
const userRole = getUserRole(session?.user?.email)

if (userRole !== 'admin' && userRole !== 'teacher') {
  return <AccessDeniedMessage />
}
```

#### Assignment Type Handling
Use type guards for assignment-specific logic:
```typescript
const getActionButton = (assignment: UnifiedStudentAssignment) => {
  if (assignment.type === 'assignment' && 
      assignment.attempts_used >= assignment.max_attempts) {
    return <Button disabled>Max attempts used</Button>
  }
  
  if (assignment.status === 'completed' || assignment.status === 'graded') {
    return <ReviewButton assignment={assignment} />
  }
  
  return <StartButton assignment={assignment} />
}
```

## API Development Patterns

### Error Handling
Consistent error handling across all assignment API endpoints:
```typescript
try {
  const { data, error } = await supabase
    .from('lesson_assignments')
    .insert(assignmentData)
    
  if (error) throw error
  return NextResponse.json({ assignment: data })
} catch (error) {
  console.error('Assignment creation error:', error)
  return NextResponse.json(
    { error: 'Failed to create assignment' }, 
    { status: 500 }
  )
}
```

### Permission Validation
Always validate permissions before database operations:
```typescript
// For updates/deletes, check ownership
const { data: existingAssignment } = await supabase
  .from('lesson_assignments')
  .select('assigned_by')
  .eq('id', assignmentId)
  .single()

if (userRole !== 'admin' && existingAssignment.assigned_by !== session.user.id) {
  return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Forbidden' }, { status: 403 })
}
```

### Query Optimization
Use efficient database queries with proper joins:
```typescript
let query = supabase
  .from('lesson_assignments')
  .select(`
    *,
    lesson:lessons(id, title, slug, description),
    course:courses!lesson_assignments_course_id_fkey(id, name, section),
    student_assignments:student_lesson_assignments(
      id, status, progress_percentage,
      student:students(id, name, email)
    )
  `)
  .order('created_at', { ascending: false })
```

## Form Development

### Assignment Creation Forms
Use consistent form patterns with proper validation:
```typescript
const [formData, setFormData] = useState<CreateLessonAssignmentRequest>({
  lesson_id: '',
  course_id: undefined,
  assigned_students: undefined,
  due_date: undefined,
  published: true
})

const handleSubmit = async (e: React.FormEvent) => {
  e.preventDefault()
  
  // Validation
  if (!formData.lesson_id) {
    alert('Please select a lesson')
    return
  }
  
  // Ensure only one targeting method
  if (formData.course_id && formData.assigned_students) {
    alert('Cannot assign to both course and individual students')
    return
  }
  
  try {
    await createLessonAssignment(formData)
    onSuccess()
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Error creating assignment:', error)
    alert('Failed to create assignment')
  }
}
```

### Date Handling
Use date-fns for consistent date operations:
```typescript
import { format, parseISO, isAfter, differenceInDays } from 'date-fns'

const getDueDateInfo = (assignment: UnifiedStudentAssignment) => {
  if (!assignment.due_date) return null
  
  const dueDate = parseISO(assignment.due_date)
  const now = new Date()
  const isOverdue = isAfter(now, dueDate)
  const daysUntilDue = differenceInDays(dueDate, now)
  
  if (isOverdue) {
    return <OverdueIndicator daysOverdue={Math.abs(daysUntilDue)} />
  }
  
  return <DueDateDisplay date={dueDate} daysUntil={daysUntilDue} />
}
```

## Status Management

### Status Badge Rendering
Consistent status indicators across components:
```typescript
const getStatusBadge = (assignment: UnifiedStudentAssignment) => {
  const now = new Date()
  const isOverdue = assignment.due_date && isAfter(now, parseISO(assignment.due_date))
  
  if (assignment.status === 'completed' || assignment.status === 'graded') {
    return <Badge className="bg-green-500">Completed</Badge>
  }
  
  if (isOverdue && !['completed', 'graded', 'submitted'].includes(assignment.status)) {
    return <Badge variant="destructive">Overdue</Badge>
  }
  
  if (assignment.status === 'in_progress' || assignment.status === 'started') {
    return <Badge className="bg-yellow-500">In Progress</Badge>
  }
  
  return <Badge variant="outline">Not Started</Badge>
}
```

### Progress Tracking
Update progress efficiently with debouncing:
```typescript
import { useCallback } from 'react'
import { debounce } from 'lodash'

const debouncedUpdateProgress = useCallback(
  debounce(async (assignmentId: string, progress: number) => {
    await updateStudentAssignmentStatus('lesson', assignmentId, studentId, {
      status: progress === 100 ? 'completed' : 'in_progress',
      progress_percentage: progress,
      last_accessed: new Date().toISOString()
    })
  }, 1000),
  [updateStudentAssignmentStatus, studentId]
)
```

## Filtering and Search

### Unified Filter Implementation
Consistent filtering patterns across views:
```typescript
const filteredAssignments = assignments.filter(assignment => {
  const matchesSearch = assignment.title.toLowerCase().includes(searchTerm.toLowerCase()) ||
                       assignment.description?.toLowerCase().includes(searchTerm.toLowerCase())
  
  const matchesStatus = selectedStatus === 'all' || assignment.status === selectedStatus
  const matchesType = selectedType === 'all' || assignment.type === selectedType
  
  return matchesSearch && matchesStatus && matchesType
})
```

### Overdue Detection
Consistent overdue logic:
```typescript
const isOverdue = (assignment: UnifiedStudentAssignment): boolean => {
  if (!assignment.due_date) return false
  
  const dueDate = parseISO(assignment.due_date)
  const now = new Date()
  
  return isAfter(now, dueDate) && 
         !['completed', 'graded', 'submitted'].includes(assignment.status)
}
```

## Analytics and Reporting

### Completion Rate Calculations
```typescript
const getCompletionRate = (assignment: UnifiedAssignment): number => {
  if (assignment.total_assigned === 0) return 0
  return (assignment.total_completed / assignment.total_assigned) * 100
}

const getOverallProgress = (assignments: UnifiedStudentAssignment[]): number => {
  if (assignments.length === 0) return 0
  
  const completedCount = assignments.filter(a => 
    ['completed', 'graded'].includes(a.status)
  ).length
  
  return (completedCount / assignments.length) * 100
}
```

