## Performance Considerations

### Lazy Loading
Load assignment data only when needed:
```typescript
useEffect(() => {
  if (session?.user?.email && !initialized) {
    if (userRole === 'admin' || userRole === 'teacher') {
      fetchAssignments()
    } else if (userRole === 'student') {
      fetchStudentAssignments()
    }
    setInitialized(true)
  }
}, [session, userRole, initialized])
```

### Memoization
Use React.memo and useMemo for expensive operations:
```typescript
const AssignmentCard = React.memo(({ assignment }: { assignment: UnifiedAssignment }) => {
  const completionRate = useMemo(() => 
    getCompletionRate(assignment), 
    [assignment.total_assigned, assignment.total_completed]
  )
  
  return <Card>...</Card>
})
```